
TY  - JOUR
T1  - Out of Sight But Not Out of Mind: Managing Invisible Social Identities in the Workplace
AU  - Clair, Judith A.
AU  - Beatty, Joy E.
AU  - Maclean, Tammy L.
Y1  - 2005/01/01
PY  - 2005
DA  - 2005/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2005.15281431
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2005.15281431
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 78
EP  - 95
VL  - 30
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Invisible social identities influence social interaction in distinct ways and create unique dynamics in terms of identity management. We integrate research from the sexuality, illness, and racial diversity literature, as well as the stigma, disclosure, and identity literature, to create a generalized model of invisible identity management. We focus specifically on revealing and passing strategies of identity management and conclude by discussing the implications of invisible differences for diversity research.
AB  - Invisible social identities influence social interaction in distinct ways and create unique dynamics in terms of identity management. We integrate research from the sexuality, illness, and racial diversity literature, as well as the stigma, disclosure, and identity literature, to create a generalized model of invisible identity management. We focus specifically on revealing and passing strategies of identity management and conclude by discussing the implications of invisible differences for diversity research.
